description: Full file path to the audio file on disk.
Track title as stored in Plex.
Primary artist credited for the track.
Album-level artist (often the same as Track_Artist).
Album title.
Plex track ratingKey (unique track identifier within Plex).
Plex artist ratingKey.
Plex album ratingKey.
Plex media/stream identifier for the tracks primary media item.
Comma-separated genre tags attached to the track.
Comma-separated genre tags attached to the album.
Comma-separated genre tags attached to the artist.
Original release date reported by Plex (raw). Also accepts input as YYYY-MM-DD (also parses common variants like YYYY/MM/DD or MM/DD/YYYY) and epoch seconds.
Normalized release date (YYYY).
Audio bitrate in kbps (approximate).
Track duration in seconds.
Track number within its disc.
Disc number within the album.
Container/codec extension (e.g., mp3, flac, m4a).
File size in megabytes.
Filesystem creation time of the media file (if available); Also accepts input as YYYY-MM-DD (also parses common variants like YYYY/MM/DD or MM/DD/YYYY) and epoch seconds.
Filesystem last modified time of the media file (if available).
Comma-separated Plex collections applied at the artist level.
Comma-separated Plex collections applied at the album level.
Comma-separated Plex collections applied at the track level.
Comma-separated mood tags (track level).
Comma-separated playlists that include this track.
Your rating for the track (0-10 scale used by Plex).
Number of times the track has been played in Plex.
Count of ratings for this track in Plex (ratingCount); 0 if none.
Timestamp of the most recent play in Plex.
Comma-separated freeform labels/tags in Plex.
Embedded or fetched lyrics text (when present).
Comma-separated playlist names to add this track to (resolved via Track_ID).
Comma-separated collection names to add the album to (resolved via Album_ID or by Track_ID).
Comma-separated collection names to add the artist to (resolved via Artist_ID or by Track_ID).
Comma-separated collection names to add the track to (resolved via Track_ID).
